### Migrate Sass node_modules Imports for Next.js Turbopack

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/02-guides/upgrading/version-16.mdx

Illustrates the change in Sass import syntax for `node_modules` between Webpack and Turbopack. Webpack supported the legacy tilde (`~`) prefix, while Turbopack requires direct path imports. This snippet shows how to update `@import` statements for compatibility with Turbopack.

```scss
@import '~bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css';
```

```scss
@import 'bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css';
```

