### Enable Turbopack File System Caching in Next.js

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/02-guides/upgrading/version-16.mdx

Shows how to enable filesystem caching for Turbopack in development mode within your Next.js configuration. By setting `experimental.turbopackFileSystemCacheForDev` to `true` in `next.config.ts` or `next.config.js`, compile times across restarts are significantly reduced due to cached compiler artifacts.

```typescript
import type { NextConfig } from 'next'

const nextConfig: NextConfig = {
  experimental: {
    turbopackFileSystemCacheForDev: true,
  },
}

export default nextConfig
```

```javascript
/** @type {import('next').NextConfig} */
const nextConfig = {
  experimental: {
    turbopackFileSystemCacheForDev: true,
  },
}

module.exports = nextConfig
```

