### Configure lint-staged for ESLint in Next.js

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/05-config/03-eslint.mdx

Set up `lint-staged` to automatically run ESLint on staged Git files, ensuring that only linted code is committed. This configuration defines a `buildEslintCommand` to fix issues in JavaScript/TypeScript files before committing.

```js
const path = require('path')

const buildEslintCommand = (filenames) =>
  `eslint --fix ${filenames
    .map((f) => `"${path.relative(process.cwd(), f)}"`)
    .join(' ')}`

module.exports = {
  '*.{js,jsx,ts,tsx}': [buildEslintCommand],
}
```

